4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO DOULAS;
5 PROVIDING FOR CERTIFICATION AND REGULATION OF DOULAS; ESTABLISHING VOLUNTARY
6 CERTIFICATION REQUIREMENTS; ALLOWING THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND HUMAN
7 SERVICES TO PROVIDE MEDICAID COVERAGE OF STATE-CERTIFIED DOULA SERVICES; PROVIDING
8 RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING SECTIONS 37-1-401 AND 53-6-101, MCA; AND PROVIDING A
9 DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 4], the following definitions
14 apply:
15 (1) "Antepartum" means the period of pregnancy prior to labor and delivery.
16 (2) "Department" means the department of labor and industry provided for in Title 2, chapter 15,
17 part 17.
18 (3) "Doula" means a trained, nonmedical professional who provides continuous physical,
19 emotional, and informational support to a pregnant person during the antepartum or intrapartum period or
20 during the period up to 1 year postpartum.
21 (4) "Intrapartum" means the period of pregnancy after the onset of labor through delivery.
22 (5) "Postpartum" means the 12-month period beginning on the last day of the pregnancy.
23 (6) "State-certified doula" means a doula who has been certified by the department.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Certification requirements -- coordination with doulas. (1) A person
26 may not practice as a state-certified doula unless certified under Title 37, chapter 1, and [sections 1 through 4].
27 (2) A doula may voluntarily apply for certification from the department under this section.
28 (3) The department shall certify a person as a state-certified doula if the person pays the fees
