1 prescribed by the department and:
2 (a) submits a completed application as required by the department;
3 (b) satisfactorily completes competencies that meet the requirements established by the
4 department by rule;
5 (c) has not engaged in unprofessional conduct as defined in 37-1-410; and
6 (d) is not currently subject to any disciplinary proceedings.
7 (4) The department shall coordinate with doulas to establish certification requirements and oversee
8 the certification of state-certified doulas.
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Voluntary certification -- practice as doula without certification
11 permitted. Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] prohibits a person from practicing as a doula without obtaining
12 certification under [section 2].
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Rulemaking. The department shall adopt rules necessary to carry out
15 the provisions of [sections 1 through 4].
